WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.599 --> 00:00:06.370
mna: This week, a task force

00:00:06.504 --> 00:00:07.205
dedicated to fighting

00:00:07.205 --> 00:00:07.572
antisemitism

00:00:07.705 --> 00:00:08.339
reportedly decided to sever ties

00:00:08.472 --> 00:00:09.207
with the conservative heritage

00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:10.441
foundation.

00:00:10.575 --> 00:00:12.210
It comes after the think tank's

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:13.544
president, Kevin Roberts,

00:00:13.678 --> 00:00:14.779
defended tucker Carlson's

00:00:15.213 --> 00:00:15.746
interview with a far-right,

00:00:15.880 --> 00:00:18.349
antisemitic activist.

00:00:18.482 --> 00:00:19.450
This infighting has laid bare a

00:00:19.584 --> 00:00:20.551
growing schism within

00:00:20.685 --> 00:00:22.220
conservative circles

00:00:22.253 --> 00:00:22.820
over how to address

00:00:23.221 --> 00:00:24.222
antisemitism.

00:00:24.288 --> 00:00:29.227
William brangham reports.

00:00:29.227 --> 00:00:33.231
&gt;&gt; Nick Fuentes, thank you for

00:00:33.231 --> 00:00:33.431
doing this.

00:00:33.564 --> 00:00:34.699
William: The interview, which

00:00:36.667 --> 00:00:37.501
lasted over two hours, was

00:00:37.635 --> 00:00:38.302
posted late last month and has

00:00:38.436 --> 00:00:40.238
been seen over 20 million times.

00:00:40.238 --> 00:00:40.905
The conservative commentator

00:00:41.239 --> 00:00:42.573
tucker Carlson, interviewing

00:00:42.707 --> 00:00:46.244
Nick Fuentes, the 27 year-old

00:00:46.244 --> 00:00:46.711
hard-right influencer with

00:00:46.844 --> 00:00:47.578
millions of followers known as

00:00:47.712 --> 00:00:49.313
"Groypers."

00:00:49.447 --> 00:00:50.248
Fuentes is known for his open

00:00:50.248 --> 00:00:51.616
racism.

00:00:51.749 --> 00:00:55.853
&gt;&gt; White people have a special

00:00:56.254 --> 00:00:56.420
heritage as Americans.

00:00:57.255 --> 00:00:58.623
William: His misogyny, like when

00:00:58.756 --> 00:00:59.390
he wrote "Your body, my choice"

00:00:59.523 --> 00:01:01.259
after the 2024 election.

00:01:03.261 --> 00:01:05.263
Nick: The whole political system

00:01:05.329 --> 00:01:06.297
is just based around women never

00:01:06.430 --> 00:01:07.465
being accountable for any of

00:01:07.598 --> 00:01:10.268
their choices.

00:01:10.268 --> 00:01:11.636
William: And his overt

00:01:11.769 --> 00:01:13.271
anti-semitism, ranging from

00:01:13.271 --> 00:01:14.805
holocaust denial, to his belief

00:01:14.939 --> 00:01:19.277
in a global jewish conspiracy.

00:01:19.310 --> 00:01:20.278
Nick: A big challenge to that,

00:01:20.278 --> 00:01:21.345
is organized jewry in America.

00:01:21.479 --> 00:01:23.914
William: The interview with

00:01:24.315 --> 00:01:25.283
Carlson drew quick, sharp

00:01:25.283 --> 00:01:25.816
condemnation from many in the

00:01:27.285 --> 00:01:29.287
conservative movement.

00:01:29.287 --> 00:01:29.820
Ben Shapiro, editor of the

00:01:29.954 --> 00:01:31.822
conservative daily wire, wrote:

00:01:31.956 --> 00:01:32.823
"No to the groypers, no to the

00:01:32.957 --> 00:01:35.293
cowards like tucker Carlson who

00:01:35.426 --> 00:01:37.295
normalize their trash."

00:01:38.562 --> 00:01:40.298
&gt;&gt; Christians can critique the

00:01:40.298 --> 00:01:40.798
state of Israel without being

00:01:40.931 --> 00:01:41.866
antisemitic.

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:43.434
William: But Kevin Roberts, head

00:01:43.567 --> 00:01:44.302
of the heritage foundation,

00:01:44.368 --> 00:01:47.305
defended Carlson.

00:01:47.371 --> 00:01:48.306
Heritage is the influential

00:01:48.339 --> 00:01:50.374
conservative think tank behind

00:01:50.508 --> 00:01:52.410
project 2025, and which has long

00:01:52.543 --> 00:01:53.411
supported Israel, and America's

00:01:53.544 --> 00:01:55.813
support for it.

00:01:55.946 --> 00:01:56.614
Roberts argued attacking Carlson

00:01:56.747 --> 00:01:59.317
was a distraction.

00:01:59.317 --> 00:02:00.484
&gt;&gt; The venomous coalition

00:02:00.618 --> 00:02:01.319
attacking him are sowing

00:02:01.319 --> 00:02:02.486
division.

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:03.321
Their attempt to cancel him will

00:02:03.454 --> 00:02:06.824
fail.

00:02:06.957 --> 00:02:07.892
Most importantly, the American

00:02:08.326 --> 00:02:09.560
people expect us to be focusing

00:02:09.694 --> 00:02:10.828
on our political adversaries on

00:02:10.961 --> 00:02:11.662
the left, not attacking our

00:02:11.796 --> 00:02:15.333
friends on the right.

00:02:15.333 --> 00:02:18.469
William: Roberts faced a strong

00:02:18.602 --> 00:02:20.371
backlash, including from

00:02:20.504 --> 00:02:21.339
staffers within heritage, and

00:02:21.339 --> 00:02:22.473
calls for his resignation.

00:02:22.606 --> 00:02:23.341
He later apologized, and

00:02:23.341 --> 00:02:23.908
denounced Nick Fuentes

00:02:24.342 --> 00:02:25.910
specifically.

00:02:26.344 --> 00:02:27.345
But the controversy has revealed

00:02:27.478 --> 00:02:30.581
the ongoing challenge of

00:02:30.715 --> 00:02:31.349
balancing different factions

00:02:31.415 --> 00:02:32.516
within the Maga base.

00:02:32.650 --> 00:02:33.351
For the pbs news hour, I'm

00:02:33.384 --> 00:02:35.353
William brangham.

00:02:35.486 --> 00:02:37.355
Amna: For more, we're joined by

00:02:37.388 --> 00:02:38.589
Arno Rosenfeld, an enterprise

00:02:38.723 --> 00:02:40.358
reporter with the forward,

00:02:40.391 --> 00:02:41.359
a jewish news outlet, where he

00:02:41.492 --> 00:02:42.360
writes the "Antisemitism

00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:46.030
decoded" newsletter.

00:02:46.364 --> 00:02:46.597
Thanks for being here.

00:02:47.631 --> 00:02:53.437
This interview, vertical -- for

00:02:53.571 --> 00:02:56.040
tucker Carlson to invite a known

00:02:56.374 --> 00:02:56.674
holocaust denier, a white

00:02:56.807 --> 00:03:00.711
supremacist in Nick Fuentes

00:03:01.379 --> 00:03:02.380
onto his chauffeur and

00:03:02.413 --> 00:03:03.013
objectively friendly interview,

00:03:03.748 --> 00:03:05.583
what does that mean?

00:03:05.716 --> 00:03:08.419
Arno: In addition to being all

00:03:08.552 --> 00:03:09.387
the things you described about

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:11.555
Nick Fuentes, he is an

00:03:11.689 --> 00:03:13.524
incredibly influential pundit in

00:03:13.657 --> 00:03:14.392
a certain corner of the

00:03:14.392 --> 00:03:14.692
conservative movement.

00:03:16.394 --> 00:03:17.661
He has hundreds of thousands of

00:03:17.795 --> 00:03:18.396
people tune into his

00:03:18.396 --> 00:03:18.696
livestream's.

00:03:19.563 --> 00:03:20.398
He has millions of followers

00:03:20.498 --> 00:03:20.698
online

00:03:22.066 --> 00:03:23.534
I think Carlson recognized that

00:03:23.667 --> 00:03:28.406
when test -- that Fuentes is

00:03:28.406 --> 00:03:28.973
growing in influence and he

00:03:29.407 --> 00:03:29.573
wanted to harness that.

00:03:29.874 --> 00:03:33.043
He was trying to get Fuentes to

00:03:33.411 --> 00:03:33.778
align with them on trying to get

00:03:33.911 --> 00:03:36.814
the Maga movement to withdraw

00:03:36.947 --> 00:03:37.748
support for Israel and was

00:03:37.948 --> 00:03:39.417
trying to convince him to back

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:40.818
away from some of his more

00:03:40.951 --> 00:03:41.519
inflammatory rhetoric around

00:03:42.553 --> 00:03:45.022
Jews because Carlson thought

00:03:45.423 --> 00:03:45.756
that was bad for the larger goal

00:03:45.890 --> 00:03:47.892
they shared of trying to reduce

00:03:48.025 --> 00:03:48.592
Americans support for Israel.

00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:50.428
That is why Carlson had Fuentes

00:03:50.694 --> 00:03:50.828
on.

00:03:51.662 --> 00:03:53.764
It was about trying to win him

00:03:53.898 --> 00:03:55.633
over or build an alliance.

00:03:56.934 --> 00:03:57.601
I think that is what worried a

00:03:57.735 --> 00:03:59.737
lot of people, because Carlson

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:00.738
has a lot more mainstream

00:04:00.871 --> 00:04:03.808
credibility than Fuentes does,

00:04:03.941 --> 00:04:05.075
so if they are joining forces

00:04:05.443 --> 00:04:05.743
that is a concern to people.

00:04:05.876 --> 00:04:08.479
Amna: Is that shift illustrative

00:04:08.612 --> 00:04:10.714
of a split among conservatives?

00:04:10.848 --> 00:04:12.550
Arno: Absolutely.

00:04:13.584 --> 00:04:15.453
There is a real dividing line

00:04:15.453 --> 00:04:16.086
and we start to see breakaways

00:04:16.454 --> 00:04:19.623
in congress, folks like Marjorie

00:04:19.757 --> 00:04:20.458
Taylor Greene becoming more

00:04:20.458 --> 00:04:20.958
hostile to American aid for

00:04:21.091 --> 00:04:21.459
Israel.

00:04:21.659 --> 00:04:23.494
On the right especially, people

00:04:23.627 --> 00:04:26.997
like Fuentes join that hostility

00:04:27.131 --> 00:04:28.632
toward support for Israel with

00:04:28.766 --> 00:04:30.601
overt anti-semitism tropes about

00:04:31.101 --> 00:04:31.469
Jews.

00:04:31.469 --> 00:04:34.638
Amna: You had the statement from

00:04:34.772 --> 00:04:35.473
the president of the heritage

00:04:36.474 --> 00:04:37.041
foundation, stepping into defend

00:04:37.475 --> 00:04:37.808
Carlson.

00:04:37.808 --> 00:04:38.909
What do you make of that?

00:04:39.043 --> 00:04:42.913
Arno: In some respects it was an

00:04:43.047 --> 00:04:43.614
unforced error on the part of

00:04:43.747 --> 00:04:44.482
the heritage foundation.

00:04:45.483 --> 00:04:45.850
No one was asking them to weigh

00:04:45.983 --> 00:04:46.116
in.

00:04:47.485 --> 00:04:49.086
The fact that Roberts would go

00:04:49.487 --> 00:04:50.488
out of his way to defend Carlson

00:04:50.521 --> 00:04:53.491
not just as a friend, but as a

00:04:53.491 --> 00:04:53.858
legitimate voice in the

00:04:53.991 --> 00:04:55.493
conservative movement and his

00:04:55.593 --> 00:04:57.528
decision to interview Fuentes

00:04:57.661 --> 00:04:58.128
alarmed a lot of people.

00:04:59.497 --> 00:05:00.564
I think there are folks who

00:05:00.698 --> 00:05:02.500
recognize that Fuentes may be

00:05:02.566 --> 00:05:04.835
growing in influence, but he's

00:05:04.969 --> 00:05:05.503
on these dark corners of the

00:05:06.170 --> 00:05:07.171
internet and you cannot really

00:05:07.505 --> 00:05:07.771
police those very well.

00:05:09.507 --> 00:05:09.773
Carlson was booted from fox

00:05:09.907 --> 00:05:10.074
News.

00:05:11.509 --> 00:05:12.510
He's also independent right now.

00:05:13.577 --> 00:05:15.513
Heritage is still an influential

00:05:15.613 --> 00:05:17.515
gate and policy voice within the

00:05:18.516 --> 00:05:18.949
Maga movement.

00:05:20.518 --> 00:05:22.653
It's not just Carlson as a more

00:05:22.786 --> 00:05:23.921
mainstream voice than Fuentes

00:05:24.522 --> 00:05:25.923
bringing Fuentes along, but it

00:05:27.625 --> 00:05:28.692
is heritage giving their stamp

00:05:28.826 --> 00:05:29.527
of approval to Carlson.

00:05:30.528 --> 00:05:31.028
I think that is what scared a

00:05:31.161 --> 00:05:31.529
lot of people.

00:05:32.530 --> 00:05:32.997
Where are the gatekeepers?

00:05:33.898 --> 00:05:35.866
Who is going to stop this open

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:38.536
animosity toward Jews from

00:05:38.536 --> 00:05:38.836
entering the political

00:05:38.969 --> 00:05:39.537
mainstream?

00:05:39.537 --> 00:05:41.539
Amna: What about the keepers of

00:05:41.605 --> 00:05:43.207
that firewall, as it were?

00:05:45.543 --> 00:05:46.877
You've seen people like Mitch

00:05:47.011 --> 00:05:47.611
Mcconnell and Ted Cruz and Ben

00:05:47.745 --> 00:05:49.547
Shapiro come out against Nick

00:05:50.948 --> 00:05:52.683
Fontes, but now you have him

00:05:52.816 --> 00:05:53.551
being hosted on a show with

00:05:53.551 --> 00:05:53.851
tucker Carlson.

00:05:53.984 --> 00:05:55.920
Is he existing in the dark

00:05:56.153 --> 00:05:56.554
corner?

00:05:58.822 --> 00:06:01.559
Arno: I think what Carlson

00:06:02.893 --> 00:06:05.229
realized, why he brought Fuentes

00:06:08.165 --> 00:06:09.567
on, was because those

00:06:09.567 --> 00:06:09.967
gatekeepers have not been able

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:10.634
to stop Fuentes' rise.

00:06:10.768 --> 00:06:13.203
Fuentes talked about his

00:06:13.571 --> 00:06:13.871
long-standing feud with Ben

00:06:15.005 --> 00:06:16.574
Shapiro, who he said for years

00:06:16.574 --> 00:06:17.107
has been trying to keep them out

00:06:17.241 --> 00:06:18.576
of the mainstream, and it has

00:06:18.642 --> 00:06:18.909
not worked.

00:06:20.978 --> 00:06:22.079
The backlash was strong and it

00:06:22.580 --> 00:06:23.080
doesn't seem like Roberts had to

00:06:23.213 --> 00:06:23.581
apologize.

00:06:25.049 --> 00:06:25.583
Heritage has walked a bit of

00:06:25.716 --> 00:06:25.950
this back.

00:06:27.184 --> 00:06:27.818
They've been receptive to the

00:06:29.587 --> 00:06:30.988
criticism, but the fact that it

00:06:31.121 --> 00:06:31.755
even happened in the first place

00:06:31.889 --> 00:06:33.591
is a sign of how much the

00:06:33.624 --> 00:06:34.058
discourse has moved.

00:06:34.191 --> 00:06:36.594
Amna: President trump has met

00:06:36.594 --> 00:06:37.928
with Nick Fuentes at mar-a-lago.

00:06:39.196 --> 00:06:39.930
He said he did not know who he

00:06:40.998 --> 00:06:41.932
was, but he also met with Kanye

00:06:43.601 --> 00:06:44.168
west, who has been anti-semitic

00:06:44.602 --> 00:06:46.604
and pro-hitler.

00:06:48.138 --> 00:06:48.906
Is there something different

00:06:49.039 --> 00:06:49.607
about this moment?

00:06:49.974 --> 00:06:52.943
Arno: I think that is part of

00:06:53.077 --> 00:06:53.644
how we got to this moment.

00:06:55.613 --> 00:06:57.081
I think this is the culmination

00:06:57.214 --> 00:06:57.715
of years of these trends.

00:06:58.282 --> 00:07:01.919
Donald Trump in 2016 I think

00:07:02.620 --> 00:07:04.088
called the bluff of a lot of

00:07:04.221 --> 00:07:04.822
Republican politicians who have

00:07:04.955 --> 00:07:06.624
been hinting at various things

00:07:06.724 --> 00:07:07.625
but have not said them openly

00:07:07.625 --> 00:07:07.992
about immigrants.

00:07:08.125 --> 00:07:10.761
Fuentes I think has called the

00:07:10.894 --> 00:07:13.030
bluff of conservative media, who

00:07:13.163 --> 00:07:14.632
have hinted at globalists, for

00:07:14.632 --> 00:07:14.732
example.

00:07:14.865 --> 00:07:18.002
Fuentes comes out and says no,

00:07:18.135 --> 00:07:18.902
we are talking about Jews.

00:07:21.639 --> 00:07:23.140
Layer like minded in -- they are

00:07:23.273 --> 00:07:24.642
like-minded in that sense that

00:07:26.644 --> 00:07:27.911
they don't have to use

00:07:28.846 --> 00:07:29.647
euphemisms, they can just say

00:07:29.647 --> 00:07:29.680
it.

00:07:31.649 --> 00:07:32.249
It is more of a culmination

00:07:32.650 --> 00:07:32.816
rather than a shift.

00:07:34.652 --> 00:07:34.985
Amna: What does the rhetoric

00:07:35.119 --> 00:07:35.653
mean in the real world?

00:07:36.954 --> 00:07:37.655
There is a connection between

00:07:37.788 --> 00:07:39.857
what is said and real-world

00:07:39.990 --> 00:07:40.791
violence against Jews.

00:07:40.924 --> 00:07:43.961
Arno: I think what is scary for

00:07:44.094 --> 00:07:46.930
a lot of American Jews, and one

00:07:47.064 --> 00:07:47.665
thing they have cared a lot

00:07:47.731 --> 00:07:50.234
about is the maintenance of

00:07:50.668 --> 00:07:50.868
liberal democratic norms.

00:07:52.169 --> 00:07:53.837
Not a partisan thing so much as

00:07:53.971 --> 00:07:55.673
maintaining gatekeepers of

00:07:55.673 --> 00:07:58.342
polite society, maintaining the

00:07:58.676 --> 00:07:59.309
ability to say this rhetoric is

00:07:59.677 --> 00:08:01.178
beyond the pale, we cannot

00:08:01.311 --> 00:08:01.679
tolerate this.

00:08:02.746 --> 00:08:04.682
As those things break down, it

00:08:04.682 --> 00:08:08.686
is less there is a one-to-one,

00:08:08.686 --> 00:08:09.086
someone watches that interview

00:08:09.720 --> 00:08:11.689
and commits antisemitism, that

00:08:11.689 --> 00:08:13.691
may have been here and there,

00:08:13.724 --> 00:08:14.692
but it's more of the sense that

00:08:14.692 --> 00:08:15.693
if you are young person watching

00:08:15.693 --> 00:08:17.828
Fuentes, you start to think this

00:08:17.961 --> 00:08:18.295
rhetoric is ok.

00:08:20.197 --> 00:08:21.699
The idea that this will become

00:08:21.699 --> 00:08:22.299
something that folks in congress

00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:24.802
believe, that folks in the more

00:08:24.935 --> 00:08:26.704
mainstream media believe, that

00:08:26.704 --> 00:08:27.705
is what is most alarming in this

00:08:27.838 --> 00:08:28.038
moment.

00:08:29.707 --> 00:08:32.710
Amna: Thank you so much for

00:08:32.710 --> 00:08:32.976
joining us tonight.

00:08:34.712 --> 00:08:35.045
♪♪

